supportDesc.support:
Written on 136 rather brown membrane leaves, with some blemishes repaired before writing by patching or sewing, preceded by two modern paper flyleaves and a cut-down leaf from a 14th-century English sequencery on membrane of better quality and followed by two modern paper flyleaves. 

Fore- and endleaves: fols. ir-iiv, blank; fol. iiirv, text, = *1;
                              fols. Ir-IIv, blank.
